Notice # 01-390 November 19, 2001  TRANSPORTATION UPDATE   SHUTTLE SERVICE   Effective Wednesday, November 21, 2002, the two vans running from One North End Avenue to the Staten Island Ferry and the Bowling Green area have been cancelled.
The Battery Park City Authority (B.P.C.A.)
is running free shuttle buses Southbound leaving Chambers Street and Northbound leaving Bowling Green.
Information on these shuttle buses have been posted in the lobby and near the elevators in the building.
The hours of operation are as follows:  Southbound Leaving Chambers Street		Northbound Leaving Bowling Green Weekdays	6:00 a.m. - 11:00 p.m.		6:14 a.m. - 11:14 p.m. Saturday	7:00 a.m. - Midnight		7:14 a.m. - 12:15 a.m. Sunday	7:00 a.m. - 11:00 p.m.		7:14 a.m. - 11:14 p.m.
These shuttle buses effectively replicate the coverage provided by the vans.

